# pandoc-bin: use the prebuilt pandoc for man-page generation. WITHOUT this USE,
# qubes components (qubes-core-agent-linux, qubes-core-qrexec, qubes-gpg-split,
# qubes-pdf-converter, ...) pull app-text/pandoc (source, Haskell), dragging in
# dev-lang/ghc + pandoc-cli[server] — a multi-hour GHC build. Enable it for ALL
# qubes-* atoms via a wildcard so a newly-pulled component (e.g. gpg-split as a
# transitive arg) can't slip through with -pandoc-bin. USE that a package doesn't
# declare is simply ignored, so the wildcard is safe.
app-emulation/qubes-* pandoc-bin
app-emulation/qubes-core-agent-linux networking network-manager passwordless-root pandoc-bin
app-emulation/qubes-gui-agent xfce
